# SARD India: Center of Excellence Marketing Platform
## Complete Presentation Script & Speaker Notes

---

## PRESENTATION OVERVIEW

**Total Duration:** 25-30 minutes  
**Slide Count:** 19 slides  
**Audience:** Directors, Senior Directors, Vertical Leaders  
**Format:** Conversational yet professional  
**Goal:** Secure stakeholder buy-in and data participation

---

## OPENING SEQUENCE (2 minutes)
*Slides: 1 (Title)*

---

### SCRIPT - Opening

[GREETING]

"Good morning/afternoon, everyone. Thank you for taking time out of your busy schedules to be here today. I'm truly excited to share an initiative that I believe can transform how we present SARD to the world.

[PAUSE - Make eye contact with several people]

Before I start, I want to set the stage. About six months ago, as we were working on our PlayStation console projects and helping a fresher get up to speed with C#, we stumbled upon something interesting—a gap that I think affects all of us in this room.

[LEAN FORWARD - Show genuine concern]

Every time a potential new client visited, or when corporate headquarters asked about our capabilities, we found ourselves scrambling to put together presentations from scratch. Project information was scattered across different systems. Our achievements weren't visible in one place. And frankly, we weren't showcasing SARD as the center of excellence that we actually are."

---

### SPEAKER NOTES - Opening

- **Tone:** Warm, genuine, conversational
- **Body Language:** Stand at center, relaxed posture
- **Eye Contact:** Brief connection with 3-4 people around the room
- **Pace:** Slow and deliberate—no rushing
- **Key Emotion:** Show empathy for the problem

---

## SECTION 1: THE PROBLEM (2 minutes)
*Slides: 2-3*

---

### SCRIPT - The Problem

[TRANSITION]

"Now, here's what I learned from that experience, and I think you'll relate to this...

[CLICK TO SLIDE 2]

When we needed to showcase who we are—our capabilities, our expertise, our growth—we didn't have a single source of truth. We had:

- Project information scattered across multiple project management tools
- Team capabilities hidden in various HR systems
- Our achievements not documented in one accessible place
- No way to quickly answer: 'What exactly does SARD do? What have you built? Who are your experts?'

[PAUSE for 2 seconds]

But more importantly—

[EMPHASIS]

When a client or Sony headquarters wanted to understand SARD's value, we couldn't show them quickly. We couldn't show them confidently. And we certainly couldn't show them strategically.

[CLICK TO SLIDE 3]

So I asked myself: What if there was ONE place—a professional, comprehensive hub—where any stakeholder, any client, any Sony group could understand exactly what SARD is capable of? What if we didn't have to recreate the wheel every single time?"

---

### SPEAKER NOTES - The Problem

- **Tone:** Identify the pain point—make it relatable
- **Delivery:** Slightly faster, with emphasis on frustration
- **Gesture:** Use hand gestures to indicate "scattered" or "multiple places"
- **Pause:** Key strategic pause before "But more importantly"
- **Connection:** Look directly at audience to ensure understanding

---

## SECTION 2: THE INITIAL IDEA (2 minutes)
*Slide: 4*

---

### SCRIPT - The Initial Idea

[TRANSITION - Positive shift in tone]

"That question led us to develop a proof of concept—an internal dashboard for our PS4 projects. Nothing fancy. Just a way to:

- Consolidate all project and team data in one place
- Automatically pull metrics from Git for real-time insights
- Generate weekly and monthly reports without manual effort
- Give quick capability snapshots for client visits

[CLICK TO SLIDE 4]

The internal team loved it. But then something interesting happened...

[PAUSE]

Our immediate manager reviewed it and said: 'This is good. But I think you're thinking too small. What if we took this concept and transformed it into a strategic marketing tool for the entire SARD organization?'

[LEAN BACK - Show realization]

That's when the lightbulb came on. Instead of a reporting tool for PS4, why not create a comprehensive marketing platform that showcases SARD India as a CENTER OF EXCELLENCE across ALL our domains, ALL our devices, ALL our verticals?"

---

### SPEAKER NOTES - The Initial Idea

- **Tone Shift:** Move from problem-focused to solution-focused
- **Energy:** Increase energy level—show excitement
- **Delivery:** Build momentum with "Then something interesting happened"
- **Voice:** Use vocal emphasis on "CENTER OF EXCELLENCE"
- **Pace:** Vary pace—slower for emphasis, faster for excitement

---

## SECTION 3: THE EVOLUTION (2 minutes)
*Slide: 5*

---

### SCRIPT - The Evolution

"So we pivoted.

[CLICK TO SLIDE 5]

We took our initial internal tool concept and evolved it into something far more strategic and impactful.

Let me show you the evolution:

**PHASE 1 - The Initial Idea:**
- Scope: PS4 console projects only
- Audience: Internal teams
- Goal: Project visibility and reporting

**PHASE 2 - The Evolved Vision (Where We Are Now):**
- Scope: ALL of SARD—every vertical, every domain, every capability
- Audience: Sony group leaders, HQ, clients, talent market
- Goal: Strategic positioning of SARD as a trusted center of excellence

[PAUSE]

Think about what this means:

[EMPHASIS]

We're not just creating a reporting tool. We're creating SARD's strategic brand asset—a single, professional platform that tells our story comprehensively to the world.

When SIE needs to discuss outsourcing opportunities, we show this. When headquarters wants to understand SARD's capacity, we show this. When a new client evaluates us, we show this. When we're recruiting top talent, we use this.

[LEAN FORWARD]

It becomes our single source of truth for who SARD is and what we can deliver."

---

### SPEAKER NOTES - The Evolution

- **Visualization:** Use your hands to show growth/expansion
- **Pacing:** Slow down for the comparison
- **Emphasis:** Bold on "strategic brand asset"
- **Connection:** This is the "aha" moment—make sure audience gets it
- **Confidence:** Speak with conviction about this new direction

---

## SECTION 4: CURRENT GOAL (1.5 minutes)
*Slide: 6*

---

### SCRIPT - Current Goal

[CLICK TO SLIDE 6]

"So, here's where we are today. We want to build a professional marketing webpage for SARD India that positions us as a CENTER OF EXCELLENCE.

[PAUSE]

This platform will be THE go-to resource for:

- **Sony Leadership & Headquarters:** Clear visibility into what we can do and our capacity
- **Potential Clients & Business Partners:** Comprehensive proof of our expertise
- **Existing Sony Verticals:** Easy access to understand where SARD can add value
- **Talent Market:** Show why SARD is an amazing place to work

[GESTURE - Show expansiveness]

Imagine: Your vertical head gets a call from headquarters asking about outsourcing opportunities. Instead of scrambling to put together a presentation, you simply share a link. They get everything they need—our journey, our capabilities, our track record, our team expertise.

[VOICE - Conversational]

That's the vision."

---

### SPEAKER NOTES - Current Goal

- **Tone:** Paint the picture—make it tangible
- **Delivery:** Conversational, almost chatty
- **Pacing:** Medium pace with intentional pauses
- **Visual Cue:** Show the link sharing action (mime sending)
- **Emotion:** Convey relief and professionalism

